核心能力 Competence
■ 職能治療專業知識與理論
具備職能治療專業知識理論基礎，以為專業技能奠基。 Professional Knowledge and Theories of Occupational Therapy
Acuire Professional Knowledge and Theories of Occupational Therapy in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills■ 職能治療專業技能
具備職能治療專業技能，以提供個案職能表現之評估、分析與治療的能力。 Occupational Therapy Therapeutic Skills
Acuire Occupational Therapy Therapeutic Skills to Provide Evaluation, Analysis and Intervention for Clients' Occupational Performance□ 溝通表達及團隊合作之能力
培養適切溝通表達及團隊合作能力，以建立良好的醫病關係及專業團隊互動。 Communication and Interdisciplinary Cooperation Abilities
Acuire Communication Proficiency and Interdisciplinary Cooperation Abilities in order to Establish Therapeutic Relationship and Improve Professional Team Interacttion□ 獨立思考及問題解決之能力
培養具有獨立思考、臨床推理及問題解決的能力，並能終身學習。 Indipendent Critical Thinking and Problem Solving Abilities
Cultivate Indipendent Critical Thinking, Clinical Reasoning and Problem Solving Abilities, and Develop Lifelong Learning□ 創新與領導能力
培養具有創新與領導的能力，以為專業技能或研究奠基。 Innovative and Leadership Abilities
Cultivate Innovative and Leadership Abilities in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills and Professional Research 

課程概述 Course Description
       This course is designed to provide students with the basic knowledge of OT evaluation process and skills of using measurement tools which are frequently used in OT practice. PBL teaching and learning experience will be incorporated into class discussion.This course is designed to provide students with the basic knowledge of OT evaluation process and skills of using measurement tools which are frequently used in OT practice. PBL teaching and learning experience will be incorporated into class discussion.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Upon completion of this course, students will be:
1. familiar with the evaluation process and basic knowledge of evaluation,
2. able to demonstrate basic evaluation skills, and
3. able to explain the evaluation results.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction 2off3Evaluative process in Occupational Therapy4Observation & interview process in Occupational Therapy5Sensory Assessment6Visual Perceptual Assessment (I): VMI, TVPS-37off8Range of Motion Assessment (ROM-I)9ROM-II10Midterm exam (lecture and practice)11Muscle Manual Testing (MMT-I)12MMT-II13MMT-III14Developmental Screening of Handicapped Infant15Pediatric Motor Assessment: PDMS2-GM16Pediatric Motor Assessment: PDMS2-FM17Pediatric Motor Assessment: M-ABC218Final Exam (lecture and practice) 

